org.fujion.plotly.plot

Class PlotContour

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fujion.ancillary.Options
      • org.fujion.plotly.plot.PlotOptions
        • org.fujion.plotly.plot.PlotContour
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OptionMap.IOptionMapConverter, IClientTransform

    public class PlotContour
extends PlotOptions
    Options for contour plot.

    a map illustrated with contour lines, for example a topographic map, which thus shows valleys and hills, and the steepness or gentleness of slopes.

    • Field Detail

      • autocolorscale

        @Option
public Boolean autocolorscale
        Determines whether or not the colorscale is picked using the sign of the input z values.

      • autocontour

        @Option
public Boolean autocontour
        Determines whether or not the contour level attributes are picked by an algorithm. If "true", the number of contour levels can be set in "ncontours". If "false", set the contour level attributes in "contours".

        Default: true

      • colorbar

        @Option
public final ColorbarOptions colorbar
        Settings for the colorbar.

      • colorscale

        @Option
public Object[] colorscale
        The colorscale. Must be an array containing arrays mapping a normalized value to an rgb, rgba, hex, hsl, hsv, or named color string. At minimum, a mapping for the lowest (0) and highest (1) values are required. For example, "[[0, "rgb(0,0,255)", [1, "rgb(255,0,0)"]]". To control the bounds of the colorscale in z space, use zmin and zmax

      • connectgaps

        @Option
public Boolean connectgaps
        Determines whether or not gaps (i.e. {nan} or missing values) in the "z" data are filled in.

      • contours

        @Option
public final ContoursOptions contours
        Controls the display of the contours.

      • dx

        @Option
public Double dx
        The x coordinate step. See x0 for more info.

      • dy

        @Option
public Double dy
        The y coordinate step. See y0 for more info.

      • fillcolor

        @Option
public String fillcolor
        The fill color if "contours.type" is "constraint".

        Default: a half-transparent variant of the line color, marker color, or marker line color, whichever is available.

      • line_color

        @Option(value="line.color")
public String line_color
        The color of the contour level. Has no effect if "coloring" is set to "lines".

      • line_dash$enum

        @Option(value="line.dash")
public DashStyleEnum line_dash$enum
        The dash style of lines.

        Default: SOLID

      • line_dash$string

        @Option(value="line.dash")
public String line_dash$string
        An alternative in the form of a dash length list in px (eg "5px,10px,2px,2px").

      • line_smoothing

        @Option(value="line.smoothing")
public Double line_smoothing
        The amount of smoothing for the contour lines, where "0" corresponds to no smoothing.

        Constraints: ≥0 and ≤1.3

        Default: 1

      • line_width

        @Option(value="line.width")
public Integer line_width
        The line width (in px).

        Constraints: ≥0

        Default: 2

      • ncontours

        @Option
public Integer ncontours
        The maximum number of contour levels. The actual number of contours will be chosen automatically to be less than or equal to the value of "ncontours". Has an effect only if "autocontour" is "true" or if "contours.size" is missing.

        Constraints: > 0

        Default: 15

      • reversescale

        @Option
public Boolean reversescale
        Reverses the colorscale.

      • showscale

        @Option
public Boolean showscale
        Determines whether or not a colorbar is displayed for this trace.

        Default: true

      • text$array

        @Option(value="text")
public String[] text$array
        The text elements associated with each z value.

      • text$string

        @Option(value="text")
public String text$string
        Text constant associated with each z value.

      • transpose

        @Option
public Boolean transpose
        Transposes the z data.

public Object[] x
        Data points for x-axis.

      • x0$number

        @Option(value="x0")
public Double x0$number
        Alternate to "x". Builds a linear space of x coordinates. Use with "dx" where "x0" is the starting coordinate and "dx" the step.

      • x0$string

        @Option(value="x0")
public String x0$string

      • xaxis

        @Option
public String xaxis
        Reference between this trace's x coordinates and a 2D Cartesian x axis. If "x" (the default value), the x coordinates refer to "layout.xaxis". If "x2", the x coordinates refer to "layout.xaxis2", and so on.
